  One person
has died and three are fighting for their lives in hospital. This is
after a horrific accident on the M7 East Bound under the N2 Bridge. Rescue Care
operations director, Garrith Jamieson said they arrived on the scene to find
carnage. He said it
is alleged that a truck reportedly lost control and ploughed into stationary
vehicles at the intersection before it collided into the pillar. "The
impact was so severe that the trucks engine landed some distance from the
truck," said Jamieson. "The
driver was found ejected with multiple critical injuries, the Lenmed 1
Aeromedical Helicopter was called in to rapidly transport the man to a nearby
Hospital," he added. Jamieson
said two passengers in the truck were found entrapped in the wreckage and the
Durban Fire Department worked to free them. "Unfortunately,
one man had sustained major injuries and he was declared deceased on the
scene," he said. "The
second passenger was placed on a manual ventilator before being transported to
a nearby Hospital for further care," he said. One of the
vehicle drivers had also sustained minor injuries as a result of the collision. He also
said at this stage the events leading up to the collision is unknown however
SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further.